Despite red flags, hedge fund companies continued promoting Mr. Madoff's funds, leading to a massive pyramid scheme that deceived top investors worldwide.
The scandal, spanning from Tokyo to Europe, exposed a lack of oversight in Wall Street's largest fraud.
Madoff's confession to a $50 billion Ponzi scheme shocked the financial community, impacting major European banks and investors.
Regulators are investigating the widespread losses, with some investors expressing anger and disappointment.
The collapse of Madoff's company revealed systemic failures in oversight, leaving many questioning the role of government regulators and financial institutions in the scheme.
